<h2>How Affiliate Links Work</h2>
<p>When you click an affiliate link on our website, you are redirected to a third-party website. If you purchase a product or sign up for a service, we receive a commission from that company. This commission comes at no additional cost to you. You pay the same price whether you use our affiliate link or navigate directly to the website.</p>

<h2>Our Affiliate Partners</h2>
<p>We currently partner with a number of companies that offer services relevant to Americans living abroad, including providers of international money transfers, banking, insurance, VPN services, and travel and relocation tools.</p>
<p>Affiliate relationships may change over time as we evaluate services that are genuinely useful to our audience.</p>

<h2>Our Editorial Independence</h2>
<p>Affiliate relationships do not influence our editorial content, Salary Arbitrage calculator results, or country rankings. We recommend products and services based on their relevance and value to Americans living abroad, not based on commission rates. Our data and rankings are based entirely on publicly available information from independent sources including the World Bank, Numbeo, and the US Bureau of Economic Analysis.</p>

<h2>FTC Disclosure</h2>
<p>In accordance with the Federal Trade Commission's guidelines concerning the use of endorsements and testimonials in advertising, we disclose that we may receive compensation for recommending products and services on this website.</p>

<h2>Questions</h2>
